article.linkText: Sessoms carries Binghamton over New Hampshire 68-61
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. -- Sam Sessoms had 28 points as Binghamton beat New Hampshire 68-61 on Saturday. Sessoms also had seven turnovers but only four assists. Caleb Stewart had 16 points and seven rebounds for Binghamton (7-18, 3-7 America East Conference), which snapped its six-game road losing streak. Chancellor Barnard added seven rebounds. Jordan Reed had 19 points for the Wildcats (3-20, 1-9), who have now lost eight games in a row. Nick Guadarrama added 13 points and six assists. Mark Carbone had 11 points. The Bearcats improve to 2-0 against the Wildcats this season. Binghamton defeated New Hampshire 69-58 on Jan. 5. Binghamton plays Maryland-Baltimore County at home on Wednesday. New Hampshire takes on Vermont on the road on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
